narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Class was a great econometrics bootcamp! Helped me apply that econometrics to game theory and work through real life research/data.
I feel like I already had a stats background so this class didnt really teach me anything new.
A very intuitive thinking of how to apply econometrics, particularly to IO.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Great econometrics bootcamp. I know the class got bad reviews the year prior but Professor Igami really listened to the comments given and restructured the course to make it more accessible to people who haven't taken econometrics or intermediate micro.
Not much work. Some of the things you learn are slightly interesting but as a whole its pretty slow.
Strengths: The professor and TA are very helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Good class if you want to refresh your stata skills and what you learned in econometrics.
if you want an easy class with minimal psets, this is it.
